Phase transitions are triggered by measurable economic events. The Cabinet proposes transition declarations; the Sovereign ratifies. Proposed initial trigger: Phase 2 begins when the Republic's quarterly revenue reaches 20% of subscription cost. Phase 3 begins when quarterly revenue exceeds 100% of subscription cost with three-month stability.

#article("4", "The Monthly Budget")

The budget flow begins with the Architect's earnings and ends with per-Province allocations. The structure is hierarchical and chronicled.

+ *Architect earnings* → Claude Max subscription (₹13,500/month currently)
+ Subscription → monthly usage envelope (tokens/capacity)
+ Envelope → *Architect's Personal Slice* (20% default, variable 10–30% per month) + *Republic Treasury* (80% default)
+ Treasury → per-Province operating allocations + reserve

==== Per-Province allocation

Each month, the Consul — drawing on Collector data and Intelligence Engine reports — proposes allocation percentages. The Sovereign ratifies. Example initial allocation:

